
[1]neatness

   NEATNESS, n.

   1. Exact cleanliness; entire freedom from foul matter; as the neatness
   of a floor or of a garment.

   2. Purity; freedom from ill chosen words; as the neatness of style.

   3. Freedom from useless or tawdry ornaments; with good adjustment of
   the several parts; as the neatness of a dress.
